cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.MM, cs.CL 

The paper deals with visual place recognition using convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and a new generalized VLAD layer. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the training procedure and the use of weakly supervised ranking loss, which falls under the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also mentions image retrieval benchmarks, which falls under the sub-category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Additionally, the paper uses Google Street View Time Machine, which falls under the sub-category of cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper discusses the improvement over current state-of-the-art compact image representations, which falls under the sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language).
